21/01/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament on Tuesday (20 January) adopted the bill establishing a state university in Tetovo that teaches in Albanian. 
The opposition Liberal Party and VMRO-DPMNE decided to boycott the vote after an emotional debate. 
The law was approved with 68 votes of the ruling coalition.
In other news Tuesday, a delegation led by Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski kicked off a two-day visit to France. 
The first meeting was with Crvenkovski's counterpart Jean-Pierre Raffarin. 
They discussed Macedonia's aspirations for Euro-Atlantic integration as well as possibilities for enhanced bilateral economic co-operation. 
(MIA, Utrinski Vesnik - 21/01/04; MIA-, A1 TV - 20/01/04)
